            <title>[THRIFT-2953] TNamedPipeServerTransport is not Stop()able</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2953</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A server using &lt;tt&gt;TNamedPipeServerTransport&lt;/tt&gt; cannot be stopped if the server does not see any traffic and is stuck in &lt;tt&gt;WaitForConnection()&lt;/tt&gt;. Closing and disposing the pipe stream does not work in all cases with synchronous I/O.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
